ConvertToOption.description:
Output format for the converted/generated document.
Can be a simple string (format name) or an object with advanced options (PDF password, watermark, image quality, CSV separator, etc.).

**Simple string examples:** `"pdf"`, `"docx"`, `"xlsx"`, `"pptx"`, `"odt"`, `"ods"`, `"odp"`, `"html"`, `"csv"`, `"txt"`, `"png"`, `"jpg"`, `"svg"`, `"epub"`, `"md"`, `"webp"`

**Full conversion matrix:** https://carbone.io/documentation/developer/http-api/generate-reports.html#output-file-type

**Object form (PDF with options):**
```json
    {
      "formatName": "pdf",
      "formatOptions": {
        "EncryptFile": true,
        "DocumentOpenPassword": "s3cr3t",
        "Watermark": "CONFIDENTIAL"
      }
    }
```

**Object form (PDF with multiple watermarks):**
```json
    {
      "formatName": "pdf",
      "formatOptions": {
        "Watermarks": [
          {
            "text": "Confidential - Page {#PAGE_NUMBER} / {#PAGE_TOTAL}",
            "anchor": "center",
            "rotation": -45,
            "opacity": 0.1
          }
        ]
      }
    }
```

**Object form (JPG with options):**
```json
    {
      "formatName": "jpg",
      "formatOptions": { "Quality": 80, "ColorMode": 0 }
    }
```

**Object form (CSV with options):**
```json
    {
      "formatName": "csv",
      "formatOptions": { "fieldSeparator": ";", "textDelimiter": "\"", "characterSet": "76" }
    }
```
